dcterms:description: The Fundamentals of Laparoscopic Surgery (FLS) program is a certification testing program that assesses laparoscopic surgical skills through various tasks, including pattern cutting and suturing.
dcterms:title: Fundamentals of Laparoscopic Surgery (FLS) program

dcterms:creator: J. A. Martin
et al.
dcterms:description: The Objective Structured Assessment of Technical Skill (OSATS) is a scoring system used to evaluate surgical residents' technical skills based on various criteria.
dcterms:title: Objective Structured Assessment of Technical Skill (OSATS)

dcterms:creator: Y. Gao
et al.
dcterms:description: The JHU-ISI Gesture and Skill Assessment Working Set (JIGSAWS) is a dataset designed for human motion modeling in surgical activities, providing a comprehensive resource for analyzing gestures and skills.
dcterms:title: JHU-ISI Gesture and Skill Assessment Working Set (JIGSAWS)

dcterms:creator: E. Yanik
et al.
dcterms:description: Tool motion data is collected from surgical videos to assess motor actions during surgical tasks, providing insights into the performance and techniques used by surgeons.
dcterms:title: Tool motion data
